In a saucepan or microwave-safe bowl, heat the butter, brown sugar and cinnamon until butter is melted; mix well. In a large bowl, combine the remaining ingredients. Add butter mixture and toss to coat. Place in a greased 15-in. x 10-in. x 1-in. baking pan. Bake, uncovered, at 300 degrees F for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes. Store in an airtight container.